With Udder Chaos we are doing our part to address two major challenges facing the space.

The first issue is network instability. We will be operating a validator in the first week post-mint in partnership with Shakudo. The validator staking pool will initially be funded by 7000 SOL from our mint as well as a portion of secondary sales. Rewards are redistributed to our holders and re-invested back into the validator staking pool, so that rewards grow over time. By operating a validator we are able to do our part to improve the network and provide our holders with utility that is truly sustainable.   

The second issue we are working to address is a lack of unbiased information on projects, which can make it challenging to DYOR. We will be developing and launching an NFT review site similar to Yelp, Google Reviews, or Rotten Tomatoes, called Alpha Audits. Users will review upcoming NFT projects from 1 to 5 starts on 4 different categories: utility, team, art, and community. The site will resemble an adapted token curated registry. To start we are going to take the mean and reward everyone within 1 standard deviation. This will reward 68% of the votes, removing the outliers. With Alpha Audits our main priority is to reduce the amount of obvious rugs and move away from people judging followers and discord members at metrics of success. Initially people will be incentivized to vote how they think the community will score a project. While this isn't a perfect solution, it does provide a definitive metric for deciding who and who isn't rewarded.
